article.description: Quincy Pondexter turned his final home game at Washington into a personal highlight show, helping the Huskies to a 97-68 rout of UCLA.
article.headline: Pondexter's fast start leads Washington to rout of UCLA
article.linkText: UCLA blown out by Pondexter-led Washington

inlines.body:
Pushing The Pace

When the Huskies push the pace in Pac-10 play, they win. When they lost to UCLA in January, they ran just 60 possessions; Saturday night they had 76.

Husky Possessions
73 or less 74 or more
FG Pct 42.5 45.3
Points per possession 1.01 1.12
Pac-10 W-L 2-6 6-1

article.story: SEATTLE -- Quincy Pondexter turned his final home game at Washington into a personal highlight show, scoring 10 points in the first 5 minutes, finishing with 20 and leading the Huskies to a 97-68 rout of UCLA on Saturday night. With a national television audience watching, Pondexter ripped a 3-pointer from the wing on his first shot and the Huskies steamrolled the Bruins from there. His final home appearance for the Huskies included plenty of chants from fans, a highlight-reel, two-handed windmill dunk on a breakaway and a long final ovation when Pondexter checked out for the final time with 4:25 left. Isaiah Thomas added 13 of his 17 points in the first half. Washington was up by 23 at halftime and the lead ballooned to as many as 33 in the second half. It was Washington's largest margin of victory ever over the Bruins. It was also the worst loss in UCLA coach Ben Howland's seven seasons at the school. Reeves Nelson led UCLA with 14 points and Nikola Dragovic added 13.
